For the chicken, heat a chargrill pan with a little oil and cook chicken on both sides for six minutes or until cooked through.In a separate saucepan melt the butter. Add the wine and heat to reduce by half.  Mix in the cream and mustard and reduce to make a thick sauce.To make the bean salad, mix the beans, red onion, coriander, basil, parsley and lemon rind together in a bowl.  Finally add the olive oil and mix through.To serve place the chicken on a bed of salad and drizzle over the sauce.